      "description": "Offering a museum-grade E46 M3, a pinnacle of analog engineering. This specimen features the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double VANOS for a razor-sharp 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered via a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual transmission to a factory-spec M-Variable differential. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and proactive subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity. The suspension geometry remains true, with all bushings and dampers providing the precise feedback expected of a low-mileage chassis. The original paint retains its factory depth, and the mechanical assembly is free of any fluid seepage or heat-cycle fatigue. A definitive driver\u2019s car for the uncompromising collector.",
